						<summary>

						<p>This is dated <hi rend="bold">Chālukya-Vikrama year 34, Virōdhin, Uttarā[yaṇa-saṅkrānti],</hi> corresponding probably to <hi rend="bold">A.D. 1109 December 25.</hi> (The date is not verifiable). It refers itself to the reign of the Chālukya king <hi rend="bold">Tribhuvanamalladēva</hi> and mentions a feudatory belonging to the <hi rend="bold">Chōḷa</hi> family (name lost) ruling over <hi rend="bold">Kaṇiyakallu.</hi> A certain <hi rend="italic">Perggaḍe</hi> (name lost) is stated to have made a gift of land for the service of the gods Siddhēśvaradēva and Mallikārjunadēva. The record is damaged.</p>						

						</summary>
					</msContents>
